headline: 2 Healthcare Stocks to Keep an Eye On and 1 to Turn Down
summary: From novel pharmaceuticals to telemedicine, most healthcare companies are on a mission to drive better patient outcomes. But speed bumps such as inventory destockings have persisted in the wake of COVID-19, and over the past six months, the industry has pulled back by 13.2%. This performance was significantly worse than the S&P 500’s 2.4% decline.
